sKeyword: Density . Ultrasonic speed . Excess molar volume . Liquid mixtures
Citation.sAbstract: Densities a and ultrasonic speeds u for pure diethylene glycol (DEG), 1- butanol, 2-butanol, and 1,4-butanediol and of their binary mixtures over the entire composition range were measured at 298.15, 303.15, 308.15 and 313.15 K. Using these data the excess volumes, VE, deviations in isentropic compressibilities, aks, apparent molar volumes, V O ,i partial molar volumes, V m,i excess partial molar volumes, E V m,i have been calculated over the entire composition range and also calculated the excess partial molar volumes of the components at infinite dilution, , V , E V m i . The excess functions have been correlated using the Redlich-Kister equation at different temperatures. The variations of these derived parameters with composition and temperature have been presented graphically.
Citation.sTitle: Densities, Ultrasonic Speeds, and Excess Properties of Binary Mixtures of Diethylene Glycol with 1-Butanol, 2-Butanol, and 1,4-Butanediol at Different Temperatures
